-- Kingfisher, Tata Power, Idea, JSW Steel, Jet Airways: India Equity Preview
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-07-23T02:51:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/kingfisher-tata-power-idea-jsw-steel-jet-airways-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
increased 135.92, or 0.8 percent, to 18,113.15. The S&P CNX
 Nifty  Index on the National Stock Exchange climbed 0.8 percent
to 5,441.95. The  BSE 200 Index  advanced 0.7 percent to 2,306.24.
SGX CNX Nifty Index futures for July delivery gained 0.6 to
5,478.5 at 10:39 a.m. in Singapore.  
 Airlines: India’s airports regulator expects to issue draft
guidelines on user charges for 14 airports in the country by the
end of August,  Yashwant Bhave , chairman of Airports Economic
Regulatory Authority, said in New Delhi yesterday.  Jet Airways
(India) Ltd.  (JETIN IN) gained 1.3 percent to 628.75 rupees and
 SpiceJet Ltd.  (SJET IN) increased 1.3 percent to 57.65 rupees.  
 Separately,  Kingfisher Airlines Ltd.  (KAIR IN) said its
first-quarter loss narrowed 21 percent to 1.87 billion rupees
($39.8 million) from a year earlier, according to a statement on
the Bombay Stock Exchange yesterday. The shares climbed 4.6
percent to 52 rupees.  
 Infrastructure companies: The central bank has allowed
infrastructure companies to refinance domestic bank loans
through overseas borrowings, according to a statement posted on
the website of the Reserve Bank of India.  Larsen & Toubro Ltd. 
(LT IN) rose 0.6 percent to 1,927.30 rupees and  Punj Lloyd Ltd. 
(PUNJ IN) gained 0.2 percent to 136.15 rupees.  Reliance Power
Ltd.  (RPWR IN) advanced 0.4 percent to 172.90 rupees,  Tata Power
Ltd.  (TPWR IN) declined 0.4 percent to 1,329.90 rupees and  NTPC
Ltd.  (NATP IN) increased 0.8 percent to 204.40 rupees.  
 Indo Asian Fusegear Ltd.  (INAF IN): Legrand SA, a French
maker of electrical switches and plugs, has offered to buy Indo
Asian Fusegear’s switchgear division, the companies said in an
e-mailed statement today.  
 The maker and exporter of electrical switchgear and
lighting products gained 1 percent to 103.20 rupees.  
 Idea Cellular Ltd.  (IDEA IN): The telecom company had
profit of 2.02 billion rupees for the first quarter, according
to a statement on the National Stock Exchange yesterday. The
shares advanced 1.2 percent to 65.50 rupees.  
 Lakshmi Vilas Bank Ltd.  (LVB IN): The owner of commercial
banks is in talks with Citigroup Inc. to acquire CitiFinancial
Consumer Finance India, a company that provides retail loans to
low-income borrowers, the Economic Times reported, citing an
unidentified person familiar with the proposal. Lakshmi Vilas
hired JM Financial Ltd. to carry out due diligence on the
business, according to the report. The stock advanced 0.3
percent to 97.75 rupees.  
 JSW Steel Ltd.  (JSTL IN): JFE Holdings Inc., Japan’s
second-largest steel producer, plans to invest about $1 billion
in India’s third-largest steel producer, said a person with
direct knowledge of the deal. JSW Steel shares gained 2.1
percent to 1,200.55 rupees.  
 State Bank of India  (SBIN IN): The nation’s largest lender
sold $1 billion of five-year debt, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. The 4.5 percent notes yield 290 basis points more
than similar-maturity U.S. Treasuries, Bloomberg data show. A
basis point is 0.01 percentage point. The stock increased 1.6
percent to 2,476.25 rupees.  
 Thermax Ltd.  (TMX IN): The power equipment maker was raised
to “outperform” from “underperform” by  Gagan Thareja , an
analyst at Batlivala & Karani Securities, with a price estimate
of 825 rupees. The shares rose 2.3 percent to 810.10 rupees.  
 Vishal Retail Ltd.  (VISH IN): TPG Capital and Vishal agreed
on the terms to acquire assets of the Indian company and a final
deal was deferred by the creditors of the retailer, Mint
newspaper reported, citing an unidentified person. The newspaper
quoted Vishal’s spokesman Manmohan Sharma as saying talks with
TPG were ongoing. TPG director Amol Jain declined to comment to
the newspaper. The stock dropped 0.3 percent to 52.50 rupees.  
